results.name: Number of n-vertex 8-hedrites.
comment: A k-hedrite is a 4-regular planar graph whose faces have sizes 2, 3 and 4 only and the total number of faces of sizes 2 and 3 is k.
link: Mathieu Dutour Sikiric, Michel Deza, 4-regular and self-dual analogs of fullerenes, arXiv:0910.5323 [math.GT], 2009.
results.author: _Jonathan Vos Post_, Oct 29 2009
